title: 30 MINUTE HIIT | Treadmill Workout Follow Along #IBXRunning
description:
Let's HIIT is Hard with this 30 minute treadmill workout! Follow along with coach Rachael as we are going to sweat our way through these HIIT intervals and come out the other side feeling accomplished!

30:00 minutes of run and recovery intervals

All speeds and inclines are suggestions. Please stay safe and within your comfort zone!

Join our community of runners: http://www.ibxrunning.com
Merch: https://www.ibxrunning.com/store
IBX Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/ibxrunning/
Veronica's Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/bodibyroni/
Rachael's Instragram: https://www.instagram.com/bedopefitness/

00:00 - Intro
00:33 - Warm Up
5:33 - Workout!
28:33 - Cool Down

Workout Structure:
Warmup: 5 minutes 
HIIT Workout - Repeat 8 times
      HIIT Interval: 1 minute - Speed increases by 0.2 each segment
      RECOVER: 1 minute
End with two 3-minute long runs!
Cooldown at the end!

1. Another Kind - Mindme
2. Astral Projection - Hallmore

4. Higher Than Heaven - Aiyo

6. Picture of You (oomiee Remix) - Loving Caliber

10. What to Do - Hallman

What did you enjoy about this workout? What suggestions do you have? We would love to hear from you below 👇

Mom of 6 here.  At 5:30am, I put banana bread in the oven and then jumped on the treadmill. This is my favorite video to follow. I get at least 2.5 miles in 30 minutes.  I love this channel! Thank you for helping me hit my personal goals, however my schedule changes daily ❤
Great for upcoming hiking 🥾. That final 3 mins, wow. Love your encouragement and willingness to push even more but in a nice way, tapping into our motivation. Very skilled. ❤

I absolutely love this HIIT video — especially because it's beginner friendly, but you can make it more challenging by upping the pace. I started off on the lower end of the paces,but now can complete the workout in the middle of the paces! Thank you coach Rachael and IBX Running team!!! You have helped me to love running again, and become a staple activity of my day.
Omg this was AMAZING. I almost didnt work out but your encouraging comments kept me motivated and I finished the workout!! Im so proud of myseld. Thank you IBX!!
